   - A signed integer named "g".
   - A signed integer named "h".

2. Two variables of type "struct c" are declared: "i" and "j".

3. The "main" function begins.

7. A variable of type "signed" named "p" is declared and assigned the result of the expression "l.d | -(l.f && l.d) - n".

8. The value of "p" is assigned to "i.g".
